edu.rit.pj2

Class WorkQueue<W>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.pj2.WorkQueue<W>
  • Type Parameters:
    W - Data type of the work items.

    public class WorkQueue<W>
extends java.lang.Object
    Class WorkQueue provides a queue of work items to be performed by an object parallel for loop in a multicore parallel program. For further information, see class ObjectParallelForLoop and class ObjectLoop.

    Note: For a work queue in a cluster parallel program, see class JobWorkQueue.

      • remove

        public W remove()
         throws java.lang.InterruptedException
        Remove and return the next work item from this work queue. This method will block until either a work item is available or there are no more work items.
        Returns:
        Work item, or null if there are no more work items.
        Throws:
        java.lang.InterruptedException - Thrown if the calling thread is interrupted while blocked in this method.
